  "title": "Software Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u>Software Engineer</u></p><p><strong>TeleRadio</strong> is developer of vehicle security solution and we are looking for dynamic software engineer that has a strong will and keen challenges. This position would suit those with strong interest and ability in\nsoftware architecture, algorithm design, ai implementation and have rigorous\nprogramming discipline.</p><p>Be part of our team to offer our services and support to our clients in protecting people and the infrastructure against security threats.</p><p><strong>Roles & Responsibility:</strong></p><ul><li>Analyse client software requirements and design the solution to meet their needs</li><li>Develop and/or integrate to provide a suitable security solution </li><li>Test solution, identify technical issues, troubleshoot the problem and provide rectification</li><li>Configure, deploy and test solution at site</li><li>Provide on-going support on the existing and new system</li><li>Prepare software documentation or/and user manual </li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree/Master in Computer Science, Computer Engineering or equivalent.</li><li>Well-versed with Window Development.</li><li>Proficient with C++, VB.net, node.js, mongodb, MS SQL, etc</li><li>Good knowledge of GUI-level and system-level programming involving processes and threads.</li><li>Familiar or have basic knowledge of python</li><li>Trouble shooting at site on software and hardware integration.</li><li>Self-motivated and able to work independently</li><li>A good understanding of image processing and database is an advantage.</li><li>Fresh local graduate is welcome</li></ul>",
